{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3b1656fb-88f5-44b9-92df-87eb483ea1d4","content":"There are no workflow files in the current directory. I can still give you a clear guide on the changes needed:\n\n### Switching to NuGet Trusted Publishing (OIDC)\n\n**1. On nuget.org** — register a Trusted Publisher for your package:\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Packages → your package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add your GitHub repo (owner, repo, optionally branch/environment)\n\n**2. In your GitHub Actions workflow**, make three changes:\n\n```yaml\n# A) Add id-token permission at job level\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # ← required for OIDC\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      # B) Use the official nuget-publish action with trusted publishing\n      - uses: actions/setup-dotnet@v4\n\n      - run: dotnet pack -c Release\n\n      # C) Replace dotnet nuget push + API key with:\n      - name: Publish to NuGet\n        run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg\n          --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### What's removed\n- **`secrets.NUGET_API_KEY`** — no longer needed; delete the secret from repo settings once migrated.\n- **`--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}`** — drop this flag from `dotnet nuget push`.\n\n### Key points\n| Before (API key) | After (OIDC) |\n|---|---|\n| `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | No `--api-key` flag needed |\n| No `permissions` block needed | `permissions: { id-token: write }` required |\n| Secret stored in GitHub | Trust configured on nuget.org |\n\nThe `dotnet` CLI automatically detects the OIDC token from the GitHub Actions environment when no API key is supplied and the NuGet source supports trusted publishing.\n\nWould you like me to create a sample workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bdaaba74-17ff-4f99-9309-66fa57dea761","outputTokens":490},"id":"fc38e1f8-6056-4e24-aae4-736b3858ba07","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:41:59.337Z","parentId":"fe67f4bb-f85a-40a8-8599-b8781fc55bb0"}
